Before we compute for the change in net working capital, we need to compute first the Cash flow from assets using other formula as shown below:

$$\begin{aligned} 
\text{Cash flow from assets} &= \text{ Cash flow to creditors} + {\text{Cash flow to shareholders}}\\[5pt] 
&= \text{\$17,800} + {\text{13,100}}\\[5pt] 
&= \underline{\underline{\textbf{\$30,900}}} 
\end{aligned}$$

Next, we will compute the net capital spending using the formula below:

$$\begin{aligned} 
\text{Net Capital Spending} &= \text{ Increase in NFA} + {\text{Depreciation}}\\[5pt] 
&= \text{\$46,000} + {\text{18,700}}\\[5pt] 
&= \underline{\underline{\textbf{\$64,700}}} 
\end{aligned}$$
